transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: I want to stop my prescriptions coming automatically.

Speaker 1: Sure, not a problem. I can help you out.

Speaker 2: Okay, can I please have your phone number so I can pull up your account?

Speaker 1: Yeah, 620-820-9252.

Speaker 2: Thank you, Craig. Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: 9-8-55.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much. This is your VIP status customer.

Speaker 1: And how's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I don't want it to come automatically, though, for me.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: So what we can do with your VIP status, you can pause it for up to six months.

Speaker 1: That way it keeps your prescription active and keeps you locked in at your price.

Speaker 2: And just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: I'll go ahead and pause that for you until July 31st.

Speaker 2: Okay. And then if I do it after that, I have to start over?

Speaker 1: No. So if you don't call back for a refill or pause it further,

Speaker 2: they would automatically send you a quantity of 10 refill on July 31st.

Speaker 1: So just put a little note in your calendar.

Speaker 2: I want to just – no, I don't even want that. I want to stop it completely then.

Speaker 1: Okay. I just have to let you know if you stop it completely,

Speaker 2: it's going to delete your profile and you would not be able to get refills in the future.

Speaker 1: And I did hear our prices are going to go up in about three months,

Speaker 2: so you would have to pay the new prices.

Speaker 1: But if you pause it, you can lock in your price and it would not go up.

Speaker 2: It's okay. I want to stop it.

Speaker 1: All right. No problem. You're canceled out. Have a good day.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh. No problem. Bye.
